# C++ Solution Style

LLVM formatting from `.clang-format` (2-space indent, 100 columns).

## Includes (concise)

Standalone solutions:

```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
```

Use the repo `bits/stdc++.h` when the system header is missing. Do **not** paste long explicit include lists into solutions.

`lib/` headers: explicit includes only, no `bits/stdc++.h`, named namespace (e.g. `delaunay2d`).

## File header

```cpp
// Platform Contest — Problem Title
// https://judge-url/problem/X
//
// Algorithm summary and complexity (keep short).
```

## Structure (SWE)

- Types: `PascalCase`. Functions/variables: `snake_case`. Constants: `kPascalCase` or `constexpr`.
- Internal helpers in an anonymous `namespace { ... }`.
- Prefer small structs and named functions over large global arrays when reasonable.
- `main`: fast I/O, then solve.

## Tooling

- `bash scripts/format_cpp.sh` — clang-format all C++ files.
- `python3 scripts/normalize_headers.py` — collapse STL includes to `bits/stdc++.h` + `using namespace std`.
- `python3 scripts/refactor_swe_style.py` — anonymous namespace, `kMaxN` constants, PascalCase structs, `snake_case` helpers, fast I/O in `main`.
- `make test` — build and run C++ library tests (Google Test + Buck2).

## Library tests (`tests/`)

- Use Google Test (`TEST(Suite, Name)`), not custom `main` harnesses or shell wrappers.
- Shared helpers live in `tests/support/`.
- Register new executables with `cxx_test(...)` in `tests/BUCK`.
- Test sources: explicit includes + `gtest/gtest.h`; no `bits/stdc++.h`.

## Exceptions

- IOI/grader signatures (`race.h`, `grader.h`, …) stay **before** `bits/stdc++.h`.
- TopCoder `class` shells: normalize headers only; do not rewrite class APIs.
- `lib/*.hh`: explicit includes and `std::`, no `bits/stdc++.h`.
